A chemical plant explosion in China's northeast caused a major water pollution incident in the Songhua River.
The Jilin Petroleum and Chemical Company is held responsible for the lethal chemicals spewed into the river.
Residents in Harbin rushed to stock up on water after the water system shutdown.
The polluted water reached Harbin, prompting officials to shut down water supplies.
China and Russia are cooperating to handle the pollution, with China closely monitoring the situation.
Measures are being taken to clean up the water and ensure public safety in the affected areas.
